INFECTIOUS HEMATOPOIETIC NECROSIS - BELGIUM
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Tue, 2 Sep 1997
From: ProMED-mail <promed@usa.healthnet.org]
Via: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
[see
Infectious haematopoietic necrosis - France 970811120605]
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 10, No. 35
Emergency report : Translation of a fax received on 25 August 1997 from Dr.
L. Hallet, Counsellor General, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture,
Brussels:
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 6 June 1997. Estimated
date of first infection: April 1997.
Location No. of outbreaks
Genappe, Brabant province 1
Yvoir, Namur province 1
Annevoie, Namur province 1
Gedinne, Namur province 2
Ermeton-sur-Biert, Namur province 1
Maredert, Namur province 1
Description of affected population: young and adult rainbow trout.
Total weight of fish in the outbreaks (kg):
susceptible cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
ca 5,000 ca 2,000 ca 850 ca 150 ...
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Marloie Centre for Rural Economy.
B. Diagnostic tests used: virus isolation in cell culture; virus
identification with immunoperoxidase.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: purchase of trout.
B. Mode of spread: contact with infected water and trout.
Control measures during reporting period: quarantine and movement control
inside the country; modified stamping out; screening. On the infected
premises: trout were removed and then killed and destroyed in a disposal
plant, the ponds were emptied, disinfection was carried out and a 15-day
period before restocking applied. Restocking with healthy young trout after
one month. Fattening of healthy fish. Investigations into movement of
animals.
--
ProMED-mail
e-mail: <promed@usa.healthnet.org>
